HEADWORD: Dextrorotatory
<hw>Dex`tro*ro"ta*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Dextro-</ets> + <ets>rotatory</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem. &
Opt.)</fld> <def>Turning, or causing to turn, toward the right hand;
esp., turning the plane of polarization of luminous rays toward the
right hand; <as>as, <ex>dextrorotatory</ex> crystals, sugars, etc.</as>
